  "response": "In the \"Despicable Me\" series, the Minions have a playful obsession with bananas, which is part of their comedic and quirky personality. Bananas are depicted as their favorite food, and their love for them adds to the humor and silliness of the characters. This obsession is often played for laughs, with the Minions reacting exaggeratedly when they see or talk about bananas. \n\nThe creators have not provided a detailed explanation for this fixation, but it serves to make the Minions more relatable and endearing to audiences, emphasizing their childlike simplicity and innocence. Overall, the Minions' love for bananas is a fun aspect of their character design that contributes to the lighthearted tone of the films.",
